    • Constructor Detail

      • GVRScaleAnimation

        public GVRScaleAnimation(GVRTransform target,
                         float duration,
                         float scaleX,
                         float scaleY,
                         float scaleZ)
        Scale the transform, by potentially different amounts in each dimension. Note that the scale parameters are the target scale, not a multiplier applied to the current scale. For example, if getScaleX() returns 4, animating to 2 will shrink the object, not grow it.
        Parameters:
        target - GVRTransform to animate.
        duration - The animation duration, in seconds.
        scaleX - Target x scale
        scaleY - Target y scale
        scaleZ - Target z scale

    • Method Detail

      • animate

        protected void animate(GVRHybridObject target,
                       float ratio)
        Description copied from class: GVRAnimation
        Override this to create a new animation. Generally, you do this by changing some property of the mTarget, and letting GVRF handle screen updates automatically.
        Specified by:
        animate in class GVRAnimation
        Parameters:
        target - The GVRF object to animate
        ratio - The start state is 0; the stop state is 1.
